  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "MSFXuBfeDDhzDZpqsrZJ714hxCU=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:41.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Schema\n\nEach user publishes a public profile at feed `ph:v2:profile:<address>`:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  address: \"0xadbA7C2F...\",       // Swarm signer address\n  ethAddress: \"0x...\",            // Original ETH wallet (optional)\n  beeNodePublicKey: \"02abc...\",   // Compressed secp256k1 \u2014 for PSS targeting\n  swarmPublicKey: \"03def...\",     // Wallet-derived \u2014 for ECDH key agreement\n  overlayAddress: \"abc123...\",    // Bee overlay \u2014 for PSS/GSOC addressing\n  updatedAt: \"2026-04-15T...\"\n}\n```\n\n## Role in chat/collab\n\n- `beeNodePublicKey` is the PSS recipient key. It is also the ACT grantee pubkey.\n- `overlayAddress` is the PSS target and the GSOC-signer mining target.\n- `swarmPublicKey` is the ECDH partner for wallet-level key agreement.\n- `ethAddress` enables ENS \u2192 profile lookup (ENS resolves to ETH address, and profile indexes by ETH address).\n\n## Why unencrypted\n\nThe profile feed is intentionally **unencrypted** \u2014 it serves as a user-discovery directory. Discovery without some public rendezvous point is impossible; the data here is deliberately non-sensitive (public keys and overlay addresses, not wallet private keys or personal content).",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:41.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:41.000Z"
    }
  },
